==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[nāh]]''
===Preposition===
'''nach''' + ''dative''

# [[after]], [[behind]].
# [[towards]], [[to]].
# according to.
# by the authority of.

====Phrases====
* '''ein Viertel nach sechs''' - a quarter past six o'clock
* '''nach einer Woche''' - after a week
* '''die Flucht nach Ägypten''' - the flight into Egypt

===Adverb===
'''nach'''
# [[after]], [[behind]].

====Phrases====
* '''nach und nach''' - little by little, gradually
[[Category:German prepositions]]
===Separable prefix===
'''nach-'''
# Attached to many verbs to indicate following or succession, as in [[nachdrucken]], to [[reprint]].

